Subject: [RFC PATCH v2 00/10] arm: rockchip: rk3576: BLOB-free TPL DRAM init
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

This series adds an open-source TPL DRAM initialisation driver for the
Rockchip RK3576 SoC, replacing the proprietary DDR binary blob.

Changes since v1:
  - Dropped OF_PLATDATA support for the clock driver (patches 02/03 of
    v1): not needed without confirmed size constraints, and the clock
    driver is not required in TPL as the DRAM driver accesses all
    hardware via hardcoded base addresses.
  - Dropped DDR GRF syscon DM registration (patch 04 of v1): the DRAM
    driver uses RK3576_DDR_GRF_BASE directly, not DM syscon.
  - Dropped DT additions for DMC reg spaces and DDR GRF syscon node
    (patch 12 of v1): not needed since base addresses are hardcoded, and
    dt-bindings are not yet submitted.
  - Removed TPL_OF_PLATDATA, TPL_SYSCON, TPL_REGMAP, TPL_CLK from the
    ROCKCHIP_RK3576 Kconfig imply block accordingly.
  - Fixed copyright: restored original "(C) Copyright 2024 Rockchip
    Electronics Co., Ltd." and added our line below it.
  - Removed descriptive file header block; kept copyright only.
  - Removed internal tracking references from comments.

Hardware
--------
The RK3576 DDR subsystem consists of two independent channels, each
containing one Synopsys uMCTL2 DDRCTL and one Synopsys LPDDR4/4X/5
combo PHY.  Supported DRAM types: LPDDR4, LPDDR4X, LPDDR5.

The driver follows TRM section 7.6.2 (LPDDR4, 37 steps) and section
7.6.3 (LPDDR5, 42 steps).  All hardware base addresses are hardcoded
from TRM Part 1 Table 1-1.

PHY training
------------
The RK3576 combo PHY includes a hardware training engine controlled by
SCHD_TRAIN_CON0[0] (phy_train_en) and SCHD_TRAIN_CON0[1]
(phy_train_done).  No Synopsys PHY training firmware is required.

Timing tables
-------------
Precalculated timing tables are provided as .inc files.  The values in
this RFC are TRM reset defaults (placeholders) and are NOT correct for
actual hardware operation.  Correct values require JEDEC JESD209-5B /
JESD209-4D timing parameters and the specific DRAM part datasheet.

Target board
------------
Primary target: Flipper One (rk3576-flipper-one-rev-f0b0c1) with 8 GB
LPDDR5.  The Flipper One DTS is not yet upstream; a Flipper One
defconfig will follow once it lands.

The series also enables the driver for the ArmSoM Sige5
(configs/sige5-rk3576_defconfig) as an immediately testable board.

Known limitations / TODO
-------------------------
 - Timing tables contain only TRM reset values.  Hardware bring-up
   will fail until values are calculated from JEDEC specs and chip data.
 - LPDDR5 MR1/MR2 encoding (initmr0) not yet calculated.
 - PHY vref and ODT settings use PHY reset defaults.
 - Flipper One defconfig pending DTS upstream.
 - Not compile-tested on real hardware yet.

Modelled on the RK3568 RFC series (20260517-rk3568-raminit-v1,
Pavel Golikov).

